</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,854,987]" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" box="[151,269,854,879]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,854,879]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">Mecopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. usually live on low bush and feed on leaves or flowers (
<figureCitation box="[977,1046,854,879]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[243,1333,193,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[243,1333,193,1953]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. M. niponensis, A: junior instar, B: ultimate instar, C: female adult laying eggs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2640106/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
<mcCollectionCode box="[1046,1088,855,879]" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">AB</mcCollectionCode>
). Females lay egg in deep soil with long and straight ovipositor (
<figureCitation box="[538,628,890,915]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1982,2004]" captionTargetBox="[243,1333,193,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[243,1333,193,1953]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. M. niponensis, A: junior instar, B: ultimate instar, C: female adult laying eggs." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2640106/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="elongata" authorityName="elongata (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[649,892,890,915]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="elongata" subSpecies="elongata">
<emphasis box="[649,672,892,915]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[687,892,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">elongata elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[948,1107,891,915]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niponensis">
<emphasis box="[948,971,892,915]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[987,1107,892,915]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">niponensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are common species in farm with open space in 
<collectingCountry box="[365,435,926,951]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="566">China</collectingCountry>
, but they are rare under thick forest. Because of their large body size and very loud songs, it is not difficult to find and collect them.
</paragraph>
